body:
When query params contain an optional enum, the enum values are not validated.

Here's an example Swagger spec with an optional optional_query_enum query param that isn't validated.

```
{
  "paths": {
    "/thing": {
      "post": {
        "summary": "SomePost",
        "description": "",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "optional_query_enum",
            "enum": [
              "OPTIONAL_ONE",
              "OPTIONAL_TWO"
            ],
            "required": false,
            "type": "string",
            "in": "query"
          }
        ],
        "operationId": "CreateThing"
      }
    }
  },
  "host": "connect.squareup.com",
  "schemes": ["https"],
  "produces": ["application/json"],
  "swagger": "2.0",
  "definitions": {},
  "consumes": ["application/json"],
  "info": {
    "title": "Test API",
    "version": "1.23"
  }
}
```

In the generated `restapi/operations/create_thing_parameters.go` file, the `validateOptionalQueryEnum` method passes a `*string` to `validate.Enum` instead of a `string`.

```
func (o *CreateThingParams) validateOptionalQueryEnum(formats strfmt.Registry) error {

  // NB: o.OptionalQueryEnum is a *string
  if err := validate.Enum("optional_query_enum", "query", o.OptionalQueryEnum, []interface{}{"OPTIONAL_ONE", "OPTIONAL_TWO"}); err != nil {
    return err
  }

  return nil
}
```

I would expect code that's similar to that in a params class, which does a zero check, e.g.

```
func (o *CreateThingParams) validateOptionalQueryEnum(formats strfmt.Registry) error {

  // Nil/zero check
  if swag.IsZero(m.OptionalQueryEnum) {
    return nil
  }

  // *o.OptionalQueryEnum
  if err := validate.Enum("optional_query_enum", "query", *o.OptionalQueryEnum, []interface{}{"OPTIONAL_ONE", "OPTIONAL_TWO"}); err != nil {
    return err
  }

  return nil
}
```
